rComments: Winnicki is a great professor, I had her for Spanish at Carleton U. She explains everything well, and is always willing to help out if anyone's having trouble with the class. Her lectures were interesting, and the assignments were reasonable. I would take her class again if I had to.

for a lecturer she was pretty good...and she didn't only depend on the slides...wheneva sum1 wuz confused she'd write 3 large blackboardz worth of notes on one concept...if ne thing she wuz 2 helpful...great prof tho...wouldn't mind havin her again

For someone who had never taken a single spanish class in my life, it was great to have a prof who is always concerned with whether you understand. Of course the class is entirely in spanish (or supposed to be) but she DID translate when necessary. She is very kind and helpful.

Wow this prof could not explain anything.  She read the slides.. in spanish.. and explained so fast in spanish.  It was very hard to stay focused and try to be interested.  I loved the first part of the class 1991 but i was very dissapointed by this one!
